05539nam a22008655i 9780520930520DE-B159720230529094047.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20032003cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209305207 a10.1525/97805209305202doi  a(DE-B1597)521041  a(OCoLC)56026368  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 7aSOC0550002bisacsh04a634.8/09794222/eng1 aSullivan, Charles L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aZinfandel :bA History of a Grape and Its Wine /cCharles L. Sullivan. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2003] 4c©2003  a1 online resource (248 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aCalifornia Studies in Food and Culture ;v1000tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tILLUSTRATIONS -- tFOREWORD -- tPREFACE -- tACKNOWLEDGMENTS -- t1. How I Solved the Historical Mysteries Surrounding Zinfandel— Sort Of -- t2. Sojourn in the East -- t3. Ho! For California! -- t4. Plant Your Vineyards! Begin Now! -- t5. Boom! 1872–1890 -- t6. The Haraszthy Myth -- t7. The Stealth Grape, 1891–1918 -- t8. Prohibition and the Fresh Grape Deal, 1919–1933 -- t9. The Two Faces of Zin, 1934–1969 -- t10. Of Pendulums and Roller Coasters, 1970–1990 -- t11. Fat Years, 1991–2001 -- t12. The Mystery of Origins Solved—Probably -- t13. Into the New Century -- tAPPENDIX: REGIONAL SUMMARIES -- tSELECT BIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Zinfandel grape—currently producing big, rich, luscious styles of red wine—has a large, loyal, even fanatical following in California and around the world. The grape, grown predominantly in California, has acquired an almost mythic status—in part because of the caliber of its wines and its remarkable versatility, and in part because of the mystery surrounding its origins. Charles Sullivan, a leading expert on the history of California wine, has at last written the definitive history of Zinfandel. Here he brings together his deep knowledge of wine with the results of his extensive research on the grape in the United States and Europe in a book that will entertain and enlighten wine aficionados and casual enthusiasts. In this lively book, Sullivan dispels the false legend that has obscured Zinfandel's history for almost a century, reveals the latest scientific findings about the grape's European roots, shares his thoughts on the quality of the wines now being produced, and looks to the future of this remarkable grape. Sullivan reconstructs Zinfandel's journey through history—taking us from Austria to the East Coast of the U.S. in the 1820s, to Gold Rush California, and through the early days of the state's wine industry. He considers the ups and downs of the grape's popularity, including its most recent and, according to Sullivan, most brilliant "up." He also unravels the two great mysteries surrounding Zinfandel: the myth of Agoston Haraszthy's role in importing Zinfandel, and the heated controversy over the relationship between California Zinfandel and Italian Primitivo. Sullivan ends with his assessments of the 2001 and 2002 vintages, firmly setting the history of Zinfandel into the chronicles of grape history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGrapeszCaliforniaxHistory. 0aViticulturezCaliforniaxHistory. 0aWine and wine makingzCaliforniaxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aalcohol.  aalcoholic beverages.  aamerican wine.  acalifornia vineyards.  acalifornia wine.  acalifornia winemaking.  acultural history.  aeuropean history.  aeuropean wine.  afood and drink.  afood and wine.  ared wine.  aregional.  ascientific.  aunited st